		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Movax12 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I uninstalled and tried it again and your instruction worked. Not sure what problem I had, which is why I qualified my post with 'seemed'.<br /><br />Pretty good. How do I change the colors and or font?</div><br />You'd have to edit the script (CRX is just a ZIP file, you'd have to extract that and then modify the files).<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">zzo38 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Which assemblers is it compatible with? Does it work with MagicKit?</div><br />Should work well enough with all the common dialects.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">koitsu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Neat, and pretty!  That gets me wondering if phpBB has support for that sort of thing server-side, i.e. could make a <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">[6502]</tt> tag for code and let it do the rest itself.  I'd have to read the god-awful innards I bet...</div><br />I suggested that <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=106493#p106493" class="postlink">in this post</a> some time ago. Personally I wouldn't mind a client-side solution, because it should be easier to add than a server-side one. Basically it would be just a matter of including a couple of JavaScript files, some CSS files, and adding a BBCode tag to generate a &lt;pre&gt; tag with a special class name.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Any chance of a userscript/greasemonkey version?</div><br />Nope, not from me, sorry.

		

